deck: A body builder turned actor who played the Hulk in the TV shows and associated TV movies.
description:
Comic Related Movie Roles

Hulk

Ferrigno played the Hulk (alongside Bill Bixby as David Banner) in the TV shows and the movies: The Incredible Hulk, The Incredible Hulk: Death in the Family, The Incredible Hulk Returns and The Trial of the Incredible Hulk. His fame in this role lead to cameo appearances as security guards in the films Hulk and The Incredible Hulk; he also voiced the Hulk in the movie The Avengers.
name: Lou Ferrigno

description:

name: Jeremy Renner

deck: The actor famous for playing Wolverine in the X-Men movie franchise.
description:
Comic Related Movie Roles

Wolverine

Hugh Jackman has played Wolverine in every installation of the X-Men movie franchise: X-Men, X2: X-Men United, X-Men: The Last Stand, X-Men Origins: Wolverine and X-Men: First Class (cameo). He will also be playing the part in The Wolverine and X-Men: Days of Future Past.

Other Movie Roles

Jackman is also well known for his roles in movies such as The Prestige, Real Steel, Van Helsing, and Les Misérables-for which he was nominated for an award for Best Performance by an Actor in a Leading Role.
name: Hugh Jackman

deck: Andrew Garfeild is a British Actor who portrays Peter Parker/Spider-Man in the rebooted Spider-Man movie franchise.
description:
Career

Andrew Garfield played the part of Spider-Man in The Amazing Spider-Man, and the Amazing Spider-Man 2. He took over the role from Tobey Maguire who had the role in the Spider-Man films before the reboot. Garfield is set to reprise the role in The Amazing Spider-Man 3.

Early Life

Andrew Russell Garfeild was born on August 20, 1983 in Los Angeles, California. When he was three years old he moved with his family to Epsom Surrey.

Personal Life

Andrew is currently dating his Amazing Spider-Man Co-Star Emma Stone.
name: Andrew Garfield

description: Ed Ryzowski was born, raised, and still lives in Winnipeg, Manitoba (that’s in Canada by the way). Though to be honest, with each passing frigidly cold winter he finds it harder and harder to understand why he stays there. He works full-time as a freelance colorist for various publishers. Ed is constantly working to try and expand his skills in other creative areas (including caricature work, game design, and pole dancing) while at the same time trying not to further his ever expanding belt size (an unfortunate by-product of sitting in front of a computer 12 hours a day).
name: Ed Ryzowski

deck: British fantasy writer responsible for The First Law series of books
description:
Bio

Joe Abercrombie, a native of England, is the film editor and fantasy writer responsible for The First Law series of books and short-stories.The First Law originally began as a trilogy (The Blade Itself, Before They Are Hanged, and The Last Argument of Kings), but was followed by three stand-alone novels set within the same storyworld, as well as four short stories. As a film editor, he works primarily on documentaries and live music for a variety of acts from Coldplay to Iron Maiden.A long-time fan of the fantasy genre, Abercrombie also engages with fans on the SFFWorld.com forums and at http://asoiaf.westeros.org/index.php/forum/11-literature/, a site dedicated to George R,R. Martin's Westeros books.

In comics

The original The First Law trilogy has been adapted into a comic series, published by Blind Ferret. The adaptation is written by Chuck Dixon with art from Andie Tong. The first four issues can be viewed at www.firstlawcomic.com.
name: Joe Abercrombie

deck: The actor famous for his portrayal of Agent Phil Coulson.
description:
Comic Related Movie Roles

Agent Phil Coulson

Clark Gregg played Agent Coulson in various films in the Marvel Cinematic Universe. His popularity in the role lead to the character's introduction into the 616 universe comics. His appearances in full length films include Iron Man, Iron Man 2, Thor and The Avengers; his appearances in short films include Marvel One-Shot: The Consultant and Marvel One-Shot: A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to Thor's Hammer. He is also set to appear in the upcoming S.H.I.E.L.D. TV show.
name: Clark Gregg
